{
  "texts": [
    "Requiring the certification mechanism to be more granular can force the for-profit entity to provide more information.",
    "Making the certifying party liable for misclassification may help to make the private disclosure more efficient.",
    "Cihon et al. (2021) discuss certification as a tool for reducing information asymmetries.",
    "29 Certification feeds back into the discussion about the choice of liability standard.",
    "For the types of risk covered through a granular certification system, producers no longer need to be held liable; the producers' incentive for safer AI-based systems then stems from its benefits to obtain a better position in the certification system, which provides larger returns, as long as the costs associated with faults accrue to the user (or are internalised by the user if third parties are involved)."
  ]
}